J-RT3-T3-5 is a derivative mutant of the Jurkat subclone Jurkat-Clone-E61 that lacks the beta chain of the T cell antigen receptor (ATCC).
A3 is a wild-type A3 subclone of Jurkat generated through treatment with Fas Antibody and is very sensitive to Fas-mediated apoptosis (ATCC).
I-9-2 and I-2-1 are subclones of A3 generated by treating A3 clone with ICR-191 (frameshifting mutagen) in the presence of Fas Antibody for 3-5 weeks (ATCC).
I-9-2 has a mutation in the cysteine protease caspase-8/FLICE (ATCC).
I-2-1 has amutation in the adaptor FADD (ATCC).
Jurkat-Clone-E61 is a clone of Jurkat-FHCRC which is itself a derivative of the Jurkat cell line (ATCC).
JKT-beta-del is a derivative of Jurkat isolated by cell sorting and lacks the surface expression of the T-cell receptor alpha/beta/CD3 complex. (JCRB)

BE2-M17 is a subclone of SK-N-BE-2.

UT-7-TPO is a thrombopoietin-dependent subline of UT-7-GM (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V87.11.4552.bloodjournal87114552).

U-118-MG and U-138-MG have identical VNTR, similar STR patterns and are very similar cytogenetically sharing at least six derivative marker chromosomes. (ATCC).

HeLaSF is a variant of Hela grown in serum free conditions. HEp-2 was originally thought to be derived from an epidermoid carcinoma of the larynx, but was found to contain HeLa marker chromosomes. DNA fingerprinting has confirmed it to have been established via HeLa cell contamination (ATCC).
BCG-823 was originally reported as a human gastric adenocarcinoma cell line. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of BCG-823 showed contamination with the HeLa cell line (PMID: 26116706; 28851942).
GLC-82 was originally reported as a human lung adenocarcinoma cell line from a 32-year-old female patient. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of GLC-82 showed contamination with the HeLa (PMID: 26116706).

KLM-1 and RPK-1 were both derived from the PK-1 cell line. 
KLM-1 was generated through injection of PK-1 and tumour formation in nude mice. (RIKEN, PMID: 8872523).
RPK-1 is a gemcitabine resistant sublcone of PK-1. (PMID: 22490663)

CMK11-5 is a subclone of CMK (PMID: 1391807).
CMK, CMK-86 and CMK-11-5 share high SNP identity (DOI: 10.1038/nature11003).

BE-13 and PEER show identical DNA fingerprints presumably due to cross-contamination; however, their diploid and tetraploid karyotypes are indicative of earlier and later passage numbers suggesting that BE-13 is derived from PEER, rather than vice-versa (DSMZ).
Hey-A8 and Hey-C2, are Cisplatin resistant derivations of HEY generated in athymic nude mice (PMID: 23934194).
Hs-934-T and HS-935-T were both derived from the same patient (Cellosaurus).
HCC2218-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC2218 (ATCC).

sample_treatment_details: Chemotherapeutic treatment included cyclophosphamide, vincristine, high-dose methotrexate, dexamethasone, carmustine, etoposide, cytarabine, melphalane and rituximab.  Treatment also included radiotherapy of the abdominal tumor region.

model_comments: SUM229PE was established by Stephen Ethier and distributed by Asterand (later acquired by BioIVT).  ICLAC was notified that the STR profile in Asterand's Certificate of Analysis matched SUM149PT.  Stephen Ethier was contacted to ask about this finding and confirmed that SUM229PE and SUM149PT were established from different donors.  An updated Certificate of Analysis was then issued; looking at the STR profile, the problem appears to have been corrected.  The correct STR profile is available on Cellosaurus. (ICLAC v9)

I-9-2 has a mutation in the cysteine protease caspase-8/FLICE (ATCC).
I-2-1 has amutation in the adaptor FADD (ATCC).

JKT-beta-del is a derivative of Jurkat isolated by cell sorting and lacks the surface expression of the T-cell receptor alpha/beta/CD3 complex. (JCRB)
OMM2-5, OMM2-3 and Mel-270 are derived from the same patient (PMID: 28018010).
LNZTA3WT4 was derived from the glioblastoma cell line LN-Z308 (ATCC).
GP5d has been established from the same adenocarcinoma as GP2d (ECACC).

model_comments: Dabrafenib and Trametinib resistant subclone of A375.
model_relations_comment: A375_CJ1, A375_CJ2  and A375_CJ3 are drug resistant subclones of A375.
The L3-3 cell line is one of multiple lines established by sequential passages of a human pancreatic cancer cell line COLO-357 through the nude mouse liver. (PMID: 1544114)

model_comments: RPMI-6666 was initially thought to have been derived from Hodgkin lymphoma, but is now known to be an EBV-positive B-lymphoblastoid cell line (PMID: 12592342).

model_relations_comment: CHLA-15 and CHLA-20 are derived from the same patient. (https://www.cccells.org/dl/NB_Data_Sheets/CHLA-20_Cell_Line_Data_Sheet_COGcell_org.pdf).
NCI-BL2126 is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as NCI-H2126 (ATCC).
Hs-870-T, Hs-860-T and Hs-791-T were derived from the same patient (Cellosaurus, ATCC)
A375_CJ1, A375_CJ2  and A375_CJ3 are drug resistant subclones of A375.
SEM-K2 is subclone of the SEM cell line (DOI: 10.1111/j.1365-2141.1995.tb05207.x)
BB49-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as BB49-HNC.
CP50-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as CP50-MEL-B.
HuG1-N and HuG1-PI were derived from the parental line HuG1 (JCRB).
LS-180 is a variant of LS-174T that has not been trypsinized during subculture, however LS-174T has been subcultured by trypsinization (ATCC).
WiDr has been shown to be a derivitive of HT-29 (ICLAC).

MUTZ-1 has been shown to be  derivative of NAMALWA (PMID: 19344951)
NAMALWA-PNT is a subline of NAMALWA which shows differential expression of immunoglobulin and MYC genes and of some cell surface antigens (DSMZ).
M120326_2 and M120327_3 were established from two different samples obtained from different regions of the same tumour.
JURL-MK1 and JURL-MK2 are sister cell lines derived from the same patient (DSMZ).
SCC152 was established from a recurrence of a squamous cell carcinoma which had been used to derive SCC90 (ATCC).
KCI-MOH1 is a derivative of HPAC (ICLAC).
NCI-BL2052 is a lymphoblastoid line derived from the same patient as NCI-H2052 (ATCC).

HP is a polytropic retroviral packaging cell line derived from the human fibrosarcoma cell line, HT-1080 (ATCC).
HX is a xenotropic retroviral packaging cell line derived from the human fibrosarcoma cell line, HT-1080 (ATCC).
PEAZ-1 has been shown to be contaminated wih HT-1080 (ICLAC).

MUTZ-1 has been shown to be  derivative of NAMALWA (PMID: 19344951)
NAMALWA-PNT is a subline of NAMALWA which shows differential expression of immunoglobulin and MYC genes and of some cell surface antigens (DSMZ).

model_comments: https://www.austinpublishinggroup.com/cancer-clinical-research/fulltext/cancer-v2-id1055.php

model_relations_comment: YMB-1 and YMB-1-E have been shown to be derivatives of ZR-75-1 (JCRB, ICLAC, PMID: 23136038).

model_comments: PWR-1-E was single cell clone isolated from cells derived from non-neoplastic adult human prostate cells that were infected with the Ad12-SV40 virus (PMID: 8761420).

model_relations_comment: The C2BBe1 (brush border expressing) cell line was cloned in 1988 from the Caco 2 cell line (ATCC).
Hs-294-T and A101D were isolated from the same donor tissue (ATCC).
MOR/CPR has been developed by growing the parent line, MOR, in increasing concentrations of cisplatin. (ECACC),

RWPE-2 was derived from RWPE-1 by transformation with Ki-ras using the Kirsten murine sarcoma virus.
RWPE2-W99 cell line was derived from the RWPE-2 by cloning in soft agar to select cells that show high expression of Ki-ras (ATCC). 
WPE1-NA22 cells were derived from RWPE-1 cells by exposure to N-methyl-N-nitrosourea (ATCC).
MZ1-B is a transformed lymphoblastoid line derived from the same patient as MZ1-PC (Cellosaurus).

21NT and 21PT were independent samples derived from primary tumours from the same patient.
21MT was derived from a pleural effusion sample taken 1 year after the primary tumour samples and was subsequently used to establish the cell lines 21MT-1 and 21MT-2 (PMID: 1977518). 
H16N2 was derived from normal mammary epithelial cells taken from the same patient as the 21T series cell lines (DOI: 10.1186/s13058-019-1173-5).
SNG-P and SNG-M were establised from primary and metastatic regions respectively of the same tumour (PMID: 858140).

B2-17 has been shown to be a derivitive of U251.
SNB19 has been shown to be a derivitive of U251 (ICLAC).

HEC-1-A was derived from the same patient as HEC-1 (JCRB).
HEC-1-B is a substrain of HEC-1-A (ATCC).

CEM/C1 is a camptothecin resistant derivative of the human T cell leukemia cell line CCRF CEM.
CEM/C2 is a multi drug resistant derivative of the human T cell leukemia cell line CCRF CEM.
AGR-ON is a derivative of CEM-AG, itself a derivative of CCRF-CEM, selected for ability to produce CSF (ATCC).
BB49-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as BB49-HNC.
CP66-EBV is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as CP66-MEL.

model_comments: Misidentified, now shown to be a B-cell lymphoma and not from a gastric cancer (PMID: 12226758).
model_relations_comment: RF-1 and RF-48 were derived from the same patient (PMID: 12226758)
M120326_2 and M120327_3 were established from two different samples obtained from different regions of the same tumour.
Ishikawa and Ishikawa(Heraklio)02ER- were derived from the same patient.

LC-1F (Floating variant) is from the same patient as LC-1-sq (Lung Cancer-1/Squamous). 
LC-1-sq-SF is a variant of LC-1-sq cultured in serum-free media (RIKEN).
CGTH-W-1 is a subclone of SW-579 established in 1995 (PMID: 25877200).
RERF-LC-MA has the same DNA profile as lung squamous carcinoma cell line SK-MES-1 (JCRB).
MDA-MB-435 and its variant MDA-MB435S have been found to be cross contaminated with M14 (ICLAC, DOI: 10.1002/ijc.31067)
ICC10-6 and ICC10-8 were derived from the same individual (DepMap STR).
SNG-P and SNG-M were establised from primary and metastatic regions respectively of the same tumour (PMID: 858140).
LAMA-87 is a subclone of LAMA-84 obtained after subcutaneous transplantation of LAMA-84 cells into estrone-treated nude mice (DSMZ).
SNP and STR profiling by the Sanger and Broad Institute indicate both EB-1 and EB2 share common ancestry.
K029AX was derived from parental line K029. (Cellosaurus).
NCI-BL2171 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2171 (ATCC).
Mero-48a (Pleural Cavity), Mero-48b (Omentum), Mero-48c (Liver) and Mero-48d (Pericardium) are derived from 4 solid tumours taken from the same patient (DOI: 10.1002/ijc.2910440212).
Lines LU-134-A and LU-134-B have been shown to be related (RIKEN).
NK-92MI is an interleukin 2 independent Natural Killer Cell line derived from the NK-92 by transfection (ATCC).

P3HR-1 is a clonally derived subline of Jiyoye.
2B8 is a HAT sensitive fusion cell line derived from the P3HR-1 (ATCC).
Hs-688A-T was derived from the primary tumour and Hs-688B-T was derived from a lymph node metastasis in the same patient. (ATCC).
HCC-827-GR5 is a Gefitinib resistant clone of HCC-827. (10.1126/science.1141478).
NCI-BL2141 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2141 (ATCC).

model_comments: The cells were immortalized by transduction with human papilloma virus 16 (HPV-16) E6/E7 genes (ATCC).
Telomerase (TERT) immortalised (Cellosaurus).
model_relations_comment:
TIG-3 and TIG-3S were established from fetal lung and skin samples respectively from the same individual (DOI: 10.34425/zs000693).
TIG-3TD is a TERT-immortalised cell line of TIG-3 (Cellosaurus).

KP-1N has been shown to be a derivative of PANC-1. 
KP-1NL is a subline of KP-1N (ICLAC).
NCI-H1876 & NCI-H1882 & NCI-H1881 have been derived from the same same patient. (NCI-Navy Medical Oncology Brance Cell Line Supplement DOI: 10.1002/jcb.240630505)
MOLT-13 and MOLT-14 are simultaneous sister cell lines derived from the same patient (DSMZ).
OMM2-5, OMM2-3 and Mel-270 are derived from the same patient (PMID: 28018010).

model_comments: SCH772984 resistant subclone of A375.
model_relations_comment: A375_CJ1, A375_CJ2  and A375_CJ3 are drug resistant subclones of A375.

model_comments: The RCC4-emptyvector cell line was established from RCC4 by stable transfection with an empty expression vector, pcDNA3, conferring neomycin resistance (ECACC).
model_relations_comment:
RCC4-emptyvector and RCC4-VHL were derived from the RCC4 cell line by stable transfection with pcDNA3 and pCDNA3-VHL respectively (ECACC). 
SLR24 was shown to be a RCC4 derivative (ICLAC).
The hTERT-immortalized foreskin fibroblast cell line, BJ-5ta, was derived by transfecting the BJ foreskin fibroblast cell line with the pGRN145 hTERT-expressing plasmid (ATCC).
Lines LU-134-A and LU-134-B have been shown to be related (RIKEN).

U-118-MG and U-138-MG have identical VNTR, similar STR patterns and are very similar cytogenetically sharing at least six derivative marker chromosomes. (ATCC). 
1321N1 is a subclone of 1181N1 which itself is a subclone of U-118 MG  (ECACC).

model_comments: Allegedly established from the peripheral blood of a 40-year-old man with acute monoblastic leukemia (AML M5) at relapse in 1982 ; however, recent new data suggest derivation from acute lymphoblastic leukemia based on the expression signature (Andersson et al., Leukemia 19: 1042-1050, 2005, DSMZ).

model_relations_comment:
HP is a polytropic retroviral packaging cell line derived from the human fibrosarcoma cell line, HT-1080 (ATCC).
HX is a xenotropic retroviral packaging cell line derived from the human fibrosarcoma cell line, HT-1080 (ATCC).
PEAZ-1 has been shown to be contaminated wih HT-1080 (ICLAC).
KMS-28-PE and KMS-28-BM were both derived independent samples, pleural effusion and bone marrow, from the same patient (PMID: 11886382).

model_comments: Although derived from the blood of a patient with multiple myeloma this line has been shown to be an EBV-transformed B lymphoblastoid cell line (ATCC).

model_relations_comment: Hs-688A-T was derived from the primary tumour and Hs-688B-T was derived from a lymph node metastasis in the same patient. (ATCC).
RMZ-RC2 and RMZ-RC5 are clonal cell lines derived from RMZ (DOI: 10.1038/bjc.1986.273).

OCI-Ly13-1 and OCI-Ly13-2 were derived from the same patient. 
OCI-Ly13-1 was established from a sample taken at diagnosis whereas OCI-Ly13-2 was established from a sample obtained during relapse (DOI: 10.1182/blood.V69.5.1307.1307).

KP-1N has been shown to be a derivative of PANC-1. 
KP-1NL is a subline of KP-1N (ICLAC).
NCI-BL2122 is a lymphoblastoid line from the same patient as NCI-H2122 (ATCC).
D-425MED and D-458MED are derived from the same patient. (PubMed=1822845).

TDL-4 has been shown to be a derivative of Raji (ICLAC).
NC-37 has been shown to be a derivative of Raji by DNA fingerptrinting (ATCC).
HCC1599-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as HCC1599 (ATCC).
NCI-BL1184 is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as NCI-H1184. (ATCC)

HeLaSF is a variant of Hela grown in serum free conditions. HEp-2 was originally thought to be derived from an epidermoid carcinoma of the larynx, but was found to contain HeLa marker chromosomes. DNA fingerprinting has confirmed it to have been established via HeLa cell contamination (ATCC).
BCG-823 was originally reported as a human gastric adenocarcinoma cell line. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of BCG-823 showed contamination with the HeLa cell line (PMID: 26116706; 28851942).
GLC-82 was originally reported as a human lung adenocarcinoma cell line from a 32-year-old female patient. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of GLC-82 showed contamination with the HeLa (PMID: 26116706).

model_comments: Originally thought to be of human origin but found to be from mouse (PMID: 20143388, Cellosaurus).

model_relations_comment: AU565 and SK-BR-3 were derived from the same patient (ATCC).

COLO-818 has been shown to come from the same patient as COLO-800 (DOI: 10.1002/ijc.25242.)
COLO-800 and COLO-794 were both derived from the same patient (ECACC).

sample_treatment_details: Six courses of CAP; cyclophosphamide, adriamycin and cis-platinum.

model_relations_comment: PA-TU-8988T and PA-TU-8988S are sister cell lines established from the same patient (DSMZ, PMID:1348891).

model_comments: https://www.austinpublishinggroup.com/cancer-clinical-research/fulltext/cancer-v2-id1055.php

model_relations_comment: JHU-028 has been shown to be cross contaminated with A549 (ICLAC).
NCI-BL2077 is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as NCI-H2077. (PMID: 8806092)
LB647-PBL is a matched normal line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation from the same patient as LB647-SCLC.
MMAc-SF is a serum-free medium adapted version of the MMAc cell line (RIKEN).
COR-L23-R is a multi-drug resistant sub-line derived from the parent line COR-L23 after treatment with doxorubicin (ECACC).
Hs-870-T, Hs-860-T and Hs-791-T were derived from the same patient (Cellosaurus, ATCC)
NCI-BL1395 is a lymphoblastoid line established from the same patient as NCI-H1395 (ATCC).
OPM-1 and OPM-2 were established from the peripheral blood of the same patient (PMID: 3926660).

model_comments: Epstein-Barr virus (EBV) immortalized.
model_relations_comment: CI formerly thought of as a B-lymphoblastoid sister of CII is now deemed a subclone of CII. (DSMZ)

AZ-521 was originally reported as a human gastric cancer cell line. However, the STR DNA analysis pattern of AZ-521 is identical to the HuTu-80 cell line which was derived from a human duodenum carcinoma (JCRB).
WIL2-S is a HAT sensitive variant of the WIL2-NS cell line (ATCC).
LU-99A is a subclone of LU-99.

model_comments: Suspected to be a  B-lymphoblastoid cell line rather than a bona fide B-CLL cell line (DSMZ, PMID: 12592342).

model_relations_comment: JURL-MK1 and JURL-MK2 are sister cell lines derived from the same patient (DSMZ).

HCC1428-BL is a B-lymphoblastoid cell line initiated by Epstein Barr virus (EBV) transformation of peripheral blood lymphocytes obtained from the same patient as the breast carcinoma cell line HCC1428 (ATCC).

J-RT3-T3-5 is a derivative mutant of the Jurkat subclone Jurkat-Clone-E61 that lacks the beta chain of the T cell antigen receptor (ATCC).
A3 is a wild-type A3 subclone of Jurkat generated through treatment with Fas Antibody and is very sensitive to Fas-mediated apoptosis (ATCC).
I-9-2 and I-2-1 are subclones of A3 generated by treating A3 clone with ICR-191 (frameshifting mutagen) in the presence of Fas Antibody for 3-5 weeks (ATCC).
I-9-2 has a mutation in the cysteine protease caspase-8/FLICE (ATCC).
I-2-1 has amutation in the adaptor FADD (ATCC).
Jurkat-Clone-E61 is a clone of Jurkat-FHCRC which is itself a derivative of the Jurkat cell line (ATCC).
JKT-beta-del is a derivative of Jurkat isolated by cell sorting and lacks the surface expression of the T-cell receptor alpha/beta/CD3 complex. (JCRB)

KP-3L cells were established using tumor nodules removed from the liver of mouse that had KP-3 cells injected into the spleen (JCRB).
KP-3N was derived from parent line KP-3 (PMID: 2172194).
HEL and HEL-92-1-7 share common ancestry (PMID: 25877200).

sample_treatment_details: The patient was treated with RTG, methotrexate, adriamycin, vincristine, cytoxan, and aramycin C
treated by transcatheter arterial embolization with lipoidol plus a combination of doxorubicin and mitomycin C
